The paper deals with graph problems and their parameterized complexity. Specifically, it focuses on the directed multiway cut problem and its variants, which are classic problems in graph theory and have been extensively studied in computer science. The paper uses techniques from parameterized complexity to show that the directed multiway cut problem is fixed-parameter tractable when parameterized by the size of the cutset of the solution. This is a fundamental result in the area of parameterized algorithms and has implications for other related problems. Given the focus on graph problems and parameterized complexity, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
